</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A vigorous woody subshrub which differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procurrens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea procurrens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its erect or arching woody stems but the two species are not well-defined.
</paragraph>
